reviews.review_text: Are you kidding?? This is an excellent quality AUD!  Great work on the recording.  I'm going to continue looking for the SBD, but for the life of me I don't know why, given this'll be on my HD in a couple of hours.

fantastic quality It's almost as if a SBD has leaked through because this is sooooooo crystal clear--
A good show, too! One of those nights that is heavy on the new tunes, as it features four of them...
Post-drums Eyes?? Check it out!
Certainly worth the download-

Slouching Towards Gamma Epitaph 4 Nifty show and here's why: The post drums Eyes was a novelty and the Flora Purim addition was hot so in the middle of a ho hum and lugubrious evening, why not pick this out. And lo! Here's the lads dropping into this decidedly un-Lads like bouncy samba and Weir is finding new and tasty laid back jazzy things to say and Phil is liking it very much, the drummers are listening very hard to each other trying to hang onto this spiffy new feeling and surprise of surprises - it's Jerry who's a bit lost trying to get his freak on in this delightfully soulful and cherry little Eyes.

The show is standard fare - a treat to come in and relax for a Winter's eve - till this very charming Little Eyes comes along.  Thanks lads!
